President Obama commends the termination of BP's blown-out well in the Gulf of Mexico as an important milestone in the response to the oil spill. He acknowledges the efforts of various individuals and organizations involved in the crisis response. The massive response involving thousands of people and vessels from federal, state, and local agencies has been successful in stopping the leak. However, the focus now shifts towards ensuring the full recovery of the Gulf Coast. The President pledges to continue working closely with the Gulf Coast communities to rebuild livelihoods and restore the environment affected by the disaster.